Rivers State government on Wednesday inaugurated COVID-19 awareness creation committee. The committee is to begin street-to-street enlightenment  and  education of residents on the danger of the pandemic. The state has recorded over 248 confirmed cases, Chairman, State Government Interministarial Committee on COVID-19 Enlightenment, Paulinus Nsirim, urged members of the team, who are  volunteers to see themselves as persons recruited to save the lives of people. Nsirim urged the members to view their responsibility serioisly and put themselves in the shoes of Governor  Nyesom Wike, who is fighting the pandemic with great vigour. The Chairman, who is also the Commissioner for Information and Communications, stated that just as the Governor’s primary goal this season is to save lives, they should see their awareness creation on Coronavirus as their own contribution to save lives in the State.